and then change the vote and then we
are just sitting seeing the match.

00:27:29.910 --> 00:27:33.950 position:56%
Hey, why did you tackle him, why did
you kill the ball but it's different

00:27:33.950 --> 00:27:35.460
when you're in the field.

00:27:35.460 --> 00:27:41.090
And in that sense, and in politics,
I learned a lot, I learned a lot.

00:27:41.090 --> 00:27:43.690
&gt;&gt; Ted Robbins: You learned
a lot but you didn't stay on.

00:27:43.690 --> 00:27:48.700
You decided to stick
more with your--

00:27:48.700 --> 00:27:51.020
&gt;&gt; Roberto Canessa: Well, I had one
of my greatest chances in my life

00:27:51.020 --> 00:27:55.260
because my wife said, if you
continue politics, I will divorce.

00:27:55.260 --> 00:28:00.190
So I had to choose then, then
you have to put lots of money

00:28:00.190 --> 00:28:03.430
in the campaign and people
are asking you for money

00:28:03.430 --> 00:28:06.860
to open a new club there
and it's a different world

00:28:06.860 --> 00:28:09.340
and thing from outside.

00:28:10.810 --> 00:28:12.280
&gt;&gt; Ted Robbins: You
know, I know we're--

00:28:12.280 --> 00:28:16.050
we want to live a good
10 minutes for questions.

00:28:16.050 --> 00:28:20.270
Are we getting close or
we still get some time?

00:28:20.270 --> 00:28:21.570
Hmm? Oh, OK.

00:28:21.570 --> 00:28:22.870
So just a few more.

00:28:22.870 --> 00:28:25.380
All right.

00:28:25.380 --> 00:28:30.440
You-- one of things that--

00:28:30.440 --> 00:28:34.680
so my experience reading the
book was I got really engrossed

00:28:34.680 --> 00:28:38.520
in the crash and the survival
and everything and then you sort

00:28:38.520 --> 00:28:40.160
of brought, like I said,
you broadened it out

00:28:40.160 --> 00:28:48.240 position:56%
and wove everybody else together and
then by the time you sort of end up,

00:28:48.240 --> 00:28:53.020
you are trying to-- you say that
